About
Currently the second largest in the world, the 550-foot tall ferris wheel located at the LINQ lets you soar above Las Vegas for panoramic views of the city. Each revolution takes about 30 minutes and each cabin holds up to 40 people. The views are prettiest at night when the city is illuminated, and you can opt for a Happy Hour ticket that comes with an open bar in the cabin. Day tickets are cheaper if you are looking to save, and tickets are also included in several Las Vegas City Passes. – Tripadvisor
Duration: < 1 hour

    Nice attraction for a good view of the area. It isn't as "scary" as one might think. It takes 30 min to make its cycle so one doesn't even feel it moving. The car is also stationary so it doesn't "swing" like the old ferris wheels. I would do it at night if possible.

    I had a fantastic experience and would gladly do it again.   • Lord & Lady Jeavons

    Brilliant view!
    Went on this during the day and didn't really have to queue. Reasonably priced and really enjoyable. As you go up to board you go through a bar area where you can buy a drink and take it with you. We waited about 10 minutes to board our pod. It wasn't over crowded and went slowly enough to enjoy the view. It was really interesting and there were facts and narrative being broadcast through a speaker whilst the pod was going round. It was fun being able to see all the hotels from above and what their pools were like, and then it was announced when you were at the top and highest point. The view over towards the mountains was breathtaking. This was well worth the price paid and we took lots of memorable photos. Enjoying a cocktail whilst going round was an added bonus!

  • cdaughe
    794 contributions
    Incredible views at night
    The High Roller gave us an amazing view of the Strip. We went about 8 pm in the evening. We could see Las Vegas in all directions especially the Sphere - which was always changing and the Bellagio fountains. It was reasonably priced in relation to the other view options ( Strat and Eiffel Tower) and I feel we got a better view to take pics. I would definitely recommend doing this. You have to commit about 45 minutes - some time for entry and 30 minutes for the ride. My suggestions are to try to time the trip so that 10-15 minutes into it ( when you will be at the highest point of the rise) the Bellagio fountains are going off and find and use a 25% off coupon ( making the ride about $26 per person at night plus tax). The LVMonorail offered one if you had a current monorail ticket.
    Visited January 2024
    Traveled as a couple

Great views!
Oct 2024 • Friends
My friends and I decided to check out the High Roller while we were in Vegas. The fee was $40 after 5pm. They do take $5 for military or senior citizens. It takes 30 minutes to do one revolution. The cars that you are in are large and will fit a dozen people comfortably. I'm sure they sometimes have lots more people in them. Our car had a total of six people which was great. We could move around taking pictures of the city as we got higher and higher. We could see the sphere perfectly. We could also see the fountains at the Bellagio, beyond the current construction on the strip.

This was a nice one-time ride to see the sites.
